comment.author: 32162360@N00
comment._content: This photo seems to be taken from the site of the 1878 Imperial Hotel - hotelimperial.com.au/the-hotel/history-2/ - looking NNE towards the Railway Station. The Royal Hotel (see note) was replaced by the Mount Victoria Hotel in 1914 (now the Victoria and Albert Guesthouse), and the terrace of four houses (No.22, Old Bank Building 1885) on the left of Station Street are not yet built either. Hence the c.1875 date? GoogleMapsStreetView

comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/beachcomberaustralia] The c. 1875 date came from notations given while in the custody of State Rail Archives - not sure of their reasoning but it may well have been the same as yours.
